Oh, no, they didn't.

36:28.447 --> 36:31.232
This is some next level
All About Evecrap.

36:31.276 --> 36:33.321
I knew
they were all jealous of me,

36:33.365 --> 36:35.105
but this is not cool, guys.

36:35.149 --> 36:37.107
Not cool!

36:39.936 --> 36:41.460
♪ Till the day when ♪ Do-do-do, do-do, do♪

36:41.503 --> 36:43.331
♪ You know on my door ♪ Do-do-do, do-do...♪

36:43.375 --> 36:46.639
Yo, did... did I just vanquish
my first demon?

36:46.682 --> 36:49.685
Affirmative.

36:49.729 --> 36:52.775
Where...? Where am I?

36:52.819 --> 36:54.429
What happened?

36:54.473 --> 36:56.214
You're just a
little jet lagged.

36:56.257 --> 36:59.260
Your trip to Greece
really did a number on you.

36:59.304 --> 37:02.916
Come on. You're just
in time to take a bow.

37:12.404 --> 37:14.580
Niko looked good.
Happy, even.

37:14.623 --> 37:16.582
She didn't
recognize you at all?

37:16.625 --> 37:18.366
No.

37:18.410 --> 37:20.586
It reminded me that sometimes
we lie to protect people,

37:20.629 --> 37:23.458
and that doesn't mean
that we don't love them.

37:23.502 --> 37:26.113
I'm choosing to believe
that that's what Mom did.

37:26.156 --> 37:30.204
Hey, so, Macy--
those letters.

37:31.771 --> 37:33.947
I think I'm finally
ready to read them

37:33.990 --> 37:37.211
if you'd still, you know,
share them with me.

37:37.255 --> 37:39.344
Yes. They're up
in Mom's room.

37:39.387 --> 37:41.781
Do you want to come?

37:43.565 --> 37:46.742
I had you to myself
for 18 years.

37:46.786 --> 37:49.397
You guys should do this
on your own.

37:49.441 --> 37:51.834
And besides, there's something
else that I need to do.

37:51.878 --> 37:53.358
Thank you.

37:53.401 --> 37:55.534
Yeah.
Come.

37:55.577 --> 37:58.363
Okay.

38:03.281 --> 38:05.674
I have to tell you.

38:05.718 --> 38:09.069
The woman from the bar--
I think she's a PI

38:09.112 --> 38:10.940
who was hired
to track you down.

38:10.984 --> 38:12.638
She thinks
you're in a cult?

38:13.682 --> 38:16.642
That must be my parents.

38:16.685 --> 38:18.905
Thanks for telling me that.

38:20.689 --> 38:24.084
That's not the whole truth
I'm here to tell you, though.

38:24.127 --> 38:28.044
That woman from the bar--
she's not nobody.

38:28.088 --> 38:30.960
She's my ex.

38:31.004 --> 38:33.659
The PI is your ex?

38:33.702 --> 38:36.357
She wasn't a PI
when I knew her.

38:36.401 --> 38:38.968
Well, we've
all got a past.

38:43.146 --> 38:45.497
I got your message.

38:53.983 --> 38:56.159
Hey, what's wrong?

38:58.248 --> 39:01.382
Oh, this past week,

39:01.426 --> 39:04.429
I've been...

39:04.472 --> 39:07.083
distracted from my work.

39:07.127 --> 39:10.391
Oh, God,
did I make a mistake

39:10.435 --> 39:13.002
telling you
about your son?

39:13.046 --> 39:17.267
No. No. I've been writing down
every last detail I can recall

39:17.311 --> 39:19.400
from those memories
while they're still fresh.

39:19.444 --> 39:22.316
Anything that might
help me one day find him.

39:22.360 --> 39:27.408
Those are natural feelings
for a parent to have, hmm?

39:27.452 --> 39:31.064
But you know
your commitment--

39:31.107 --> 39:33.153
it has to be...To the Charmed Ones.

39:35.155 --> 39:37.157
Yes, I know.

39:38.724 --> 39:41.074
I'm...

39:41.117 --> 39:43.642
not the man I was
before Tartarus.

39:45.557 --> 39:47.820
And the slate's no longer
clean, you might say.

39:50.475 --> 39:53.652
The fact is,

39:53.695 --> 39:56.829
I'm not sure I can be
their Whitelighter anymore.

40:00.093 --> 40:02.443
They should be
in safer hands.

40:02.487 --> 40:05.664
But I know how much
you love them.

40:09.755 --> 40:14.542
Which is why the only
responsible thing to do...

40:14.586 --> 40:16.457
is to leave.

40:18.459 --> 40:22.507
Well, if you really
do feel that way,

40:22.550 --> 40:26.119
then... you need to tell them.

40:26.162 --> 40:28.121
Ah.

40:28.164 --> 40:30.079
You've always said
they're the closest thing

40:30.123 --> 40:32.125
to family
you've ever had.

40:34.475 --> 40:36.869
Until now.

40:36.912 --> 40:38.871
MACY:
What?

40:38.914 --> 40:40.525
Oh, my God,
did you see this?

40:40.568 --> 40:42.744
Only Macy Vaughn's father
could pull off the phrase

40:42.788 --> 40:44.398
"carnal cohabitation"
in a love letter.

40:44.442 --> 40:46.487
Man, he was not the
most expressive of men,

40:46.531 --> 40:48.750
but he was a good
father in his own way.Oh, my...

40:48.794 --> 40:50.709
I really wish
I could have known him.

40:50.752 --> 40:52.928
He would have had his
hands full with you.

40:52.972 --> 40:54.626
Excuse me!

40:54.669 --> 40:56.671
The hugging, the crying,

40:56.715 --> 40:58.717
the spontaneous
dance parties.

40:58.760 --> 41:00.893
No one can resist
my spontaneous dance parties.

41:00.936 --> 41:02.982
Yeah, Dexter Vaughn
could have.

41:03.025 --> 41:06.594
Oh, yeah, I would have
won him over.

41:06.638 --> 41:09.467
You definitely would have.

41:13.209 --> 41:15.647
What is it?

41:23.524 --> 41:25.787
"I don't regret what we
did, not for a minute,

41:25.831 --> 41:28.007
"but every time I look
at Macy, I'm reminded

41:28.050 --> 41:30.052
"that one day, she
will learn the truth.

41:30.096 --> 41:31.924
"And when she finds
out what we did to...

41:31.967 --> 41:35.014
bring her... back
from the dead..."

41:36.711 --> 41:39.018
"...I'm afraid she'll
never forgive us."

